\">univ</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Unlike the other set constructors, the `iota` definite descriptor\nis a set for any set input, but not constructively so, so there is no\nassociated `Class → Set` function. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/Class.html#Class.iota_ex","kind":"theorem","line":291,"name":"Class.iota_ex","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/Class.lean#L291-L298"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/Class.html#Class.iota_val\"><span class=\"name\">Class</span>.<span class=\"name\">iota_val</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/Class.html#Class\">Class.{u_1}</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/Basic.html#ZFSet\">ZFSet.{u_1}</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">H</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">y</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/Basic.html#ZFSet\">ZFSet.{u_1}</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">A</span> <span class=\"fn\">y</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\">y</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">A</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/Class.html#Class.iota\">iota</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">x</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/Class.html#Class.iota_val","kind":"theorem","line":286,"name":"Class.iota_val","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mat